      },
      "date": "2018-09-01 08:13:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> if (current_user_ns() == &init_user_ns)\n\nShould we add a similar check in the Lustre and ext4 code?  I believe that this is intended to prevent processes inside in VMs from changing the project ID state.  I wonder if we should be doing the same for subdirectory mounts?\n\nIt probably makes sense to submit a patch to upstream linux-ext4 to get some review and discussion about whether that is the right behaviour.  Also CC Dave Chinner <dchinner@redhat.com>, since he knows the best about the intended project quota behaviour.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
