      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nWe had some discussion at LAD to submit tests in a first patch with a special ENDEDINIRIONS value, so that the patch is *expected* to fail the checks before the fix is landed, and this would be considered a \"PASS\" for the test. \n\nThat ensures the tests are written in a way that they are detecting the actual failure, and that the \"fix\" patch actually fixes the problem being worked on. See LU-11520 for details.",
